INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (88,1,'2021-10-05 08:14:04','2021-10-05 08:14:04','<h2><b>History</b></h2>\n<h2><a href=\"http://paozupperroom.local/six_pillars/\"><b>Six Pillars</b></a></h2>\nPAOZ Upper Room Ministries is bible based Pentecostal church passionately fulfilling the Great commission and engaged in Social transformation. We are part of a network of local churches in the Pentecostal Assemblies of Zimbabwe throughout the nation Zimbabwe. The PAOZ was pioneered by missionaries from the Pentecostal Assemblies of Canada (PAOC) in 1948. Upper Room Ministries began in 1985 at Pentecost House.\n<h4 style=\"font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 0px; color: #161616; text-align: start;\" data-elementor-setting-key=\"title\" data-pen-placeholder=\"Type Here...\">Vision</h4>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\">House To Know Christ,Make Him known and Change the world.</h3>\n<h4 style=\"font-size: 19px; font-style: normal; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 0px; color: #161616; text-align: left;\" data-elementor-setting-key=\"title\" data-pen-placeholder=\"Type Here...\">Mission</h4>\n<h3 style=\"font-style: normal; text-align: left;\">We are a Bible based Pentecostal Church passionate about fulfilling the Great Commission and engaged in Social&nbsp; Transformation.</h3>\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b>People</b><b></b></p>\nWe are committed to loving people and sharing the gospel of Jesus Christ at every opportunity.(John 3:16)\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b>Fellowship</b><b></b></p>\nWe are committed to creating an environment where believers can relate to one another with genuine love and acceptance (Ephesians 2:20-22; Romans 12:4-5)\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b>Discipleship</b><b></b></p>\nWe are committed to creating an environment where believers can relate to one another with genuine love and acceptance (Ephesians 2:20-22; Romans 12:4-5)\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b>Pentecostal Heritage</b><b></b></p>\nWe are committed to seeing the person and the power of the Holy Spirit in all we do. (Mark 15:15-17; Acts 1:8; Acts 2:4)\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b>Sound Doctrine</b></p>\nWe are committed to proclaiming and practicing the whole counsel of God as found in the Holy Bible wit integrity and accuracy (Luke 24:19; Acts 1:1; Timothy 3:16; Acts 20:20)\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b>Excellence</b><b></b></p>\nWe are committed to seeing excellence exhibited in all our endeavors upholding the beauty of God (2 Corinthians 8:7; Daniel 5:12; 1 Corinthians 14:40)\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b>Integrity</b><b></b></p>\nWe are committed to transparency and honesty in all our personal, public and corporate affairs. (Daniel 6:3-4; Romans 14:16; 2 Thessalonians 5:21-22)\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b>Accountability</b><b></b></p>\nWe are committed to building Structures and practices that will enhance accountability with the understanding that God shall require us to give an account (Romans 12:14)\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b>Organizational Structure\n</b>The operation of the work and ministry of the PAOZ is carried out through its structures.</p>','About','','publish','closed','closed','','about','','','2021-10-28 16:07:19','2021-10-28 16:07:19','',0,'http://paozupperroom.local/?page_id=88',0,'page','',0);
